INSERT INTO `r_app_event_values` VALUES(23, 145, 2062, 'AlbumArtSmall.jpg', 'title', '<p align="justify" >ur little plan of bringing all the little guys across the world together to build a bigger and better Zomato has been working very well.&nbsp;The turn of events (and the subsequent market leadership) in New Zealand after we acquired MenuMania worked very well for our users, and for us as a business. The initial signs with our acquisitions in the Czech Republic and Slovakia are very good, and we&rsquo;re very excited about building on top of a great product with a great local team, which adds a ton of energy to Zomato.</p>\r\n\r\n <p align="justify" >The Czech Republic and Slovakia were our first two launches in Central and Eastern Europe (CEE); with that underway, we started thinking about Poland, definitely the largest market for a product like ours in CEE. Poland is far ahead of a lot of countries when it comes to adopting and developing new technologies (and is sometimes also said to be innovating a lot more than good old Silicon Valley).</p>\r\n\r\n <p align="justify" >Gastronauci, the newest member of the Zomato family, has had an iron grip on the market in Poland and built great market and mindshare over the past 6 years. With the brand, and the associated network effect, Zomato will have a significant advantage (and head start) compared to our other competitors. We&rsquo;re not kidding when we say that Gastronauci was doing such a great job, it was a straightforward buy vs. no-go decision for us while evaluating our foray into Poland. They&rsquo;ve beaten the yell out of any competition coming out of the Valley, which is commendable.</p>\r\n\r\n <p align="justify" >We were always really excited about the Poland market, and Gastronauci joining us just makes the excitement more real. We&rsquo;re now eagerly looking forward to making Zomato Poland the de-facto restaurant guide in the country.</p>\r\n', '2014-12-17', '02:00 AM', '2014-12-25', '03:00 AM', 'Yes', 'rgb(223,223,223)', 'rgb(28,209,228)', 'Folder.jpg');
